key "bushman_delayed_2015"

\end_inset

,Beatty and Liao, 2011; Bhat et al., 2014; Bushman and Williams 2012, 2014;
 and Nichols et al., 2009.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Conceptually, loan loss provisions and loan loss reserves can be viewed
 as providing a cushion against expected losses while bank capital is a
 buffer against unexpected losses (e.g., Laeven and Majnoni, 2003).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Delayed loss recognition creates an overhang of unrecognized losses that
 carry forward to the future, which increase the capital inadequacy concerns
 during economic downturn.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bushman and Williams (2014), 
\emph on
DELR
\emph default
 increase bank liquidity risk and systemic risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
